## Fix: Mapping Import buttons not triggering file picker (v0.4.0)

### Context
On the Mapping → Import page, clicking "From Local File" or "From Unity Catalog" had no effect.
The event listeners in `mapping-import.js` were attached with `document.getElementById(...)` at
script-load time, but the script tag appears in the template *before* the HTML partials that
render the buttons — so all three `getElementById` calls returned `null`, the optional-chaining
`?.addEventListener()` silently no-oped, and no listeners were ever registered.

### Changes

1. `src/front/static/mapping/js/mapping-import.js`
   - Wrapped all three event-listener registrations (`#importR2rmlLocalBtn`,
     `#importR2rmlUCBtn`, `#importR2rmlFileInput`) inside a `DOMContentLoaded` handler so
     they execute only after the full DOM is available.

### Modified files
- `src/front/static/mapping/js/mapping-import.js`

### Test results
- `tests/units/mapping/` — 62 passed in 0.56 s

---

